  <Name>k__BackingField: Nahum
  fancyName: 
  nickname: nam
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Anger against Nineveh"
      content: '  This message concerning Nineveh came as a vision to Nahum, who
        lived in Elkosh.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a jealous God,filled with vengeance
        and rage.He takes revenge on all who oppose himand continues to rage against
        his enemies!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is slow to get angry, but his power
        is great,and he never lets the guilty go unpunished.He displays his power
        in the whirlwind and the storm.The billowing clouds are the dust beneath
        his feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At his command the oceans dry up,and the rivers disappear.The lush
        pastures of Bashan and Carmel fade,and the green forests of Lebanon wither.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In his presence the mountains quake,and the hills melt away;the earth
        trembles,and its people are destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who can stand before his fierce anger?Who can survive his burning
        fury?His rage blazes forth like fire,and the mountains crumble to dust in
        his presence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good,a strong refuge when trouble
        comes.He is close to those who trust in him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But he will sweep away his enemies[[COMMENT(0)]]in an overwhelming
        flood.He will pursue his foesinto the darkness of night.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>sweep away her place.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "Why are you scheming against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?He will
        destroy you with one blow;he won\u2019t need to strike twice!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His enemies, tangled like thornbushesand staggering like drunks,will
        be burned up like dry stubble in a field.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is this wicked counselor of yourswho plots evil against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThough the
        Assyrians have many allies,they will be destroyed and disappear.O my people,
        I have punished you before,but I will not punish you again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now I will break the yoke of bondage from your neckand tear off the
        chains of Assyrian oppression.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says concerning
        the Assyrians in Nineveh:\u201CYou will have no more children to carry on
        your name.I will destroy all the idols in the temples of your gods.I am preparing
        a grave for youbecause you are despicable!\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Fall of Nineveh
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]Your enemy is coming to crush you, Nineveh.Man
        the ramparts! Watch the roads!Prepare your defenses! Call out your forces!  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: '  Verses 2:1-13 are numbered 2:2-14 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: "Even though the destroyer has destroyed Judah,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will restore its honor.Israel\u2019s vine has been stripped of branches,but
        he will restore its splendor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Shields flash red in the sunlight!See the scarlet uniforms of the
        valiant troops!Watch as their glittering chariots move into position,with
        a forest of spears waving above them.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        content: Greek and Syriac versions read <b>into position, / the horses whipped
          into a frenzy.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The chariots race recklessly along the streetsand rush wildly through
        the squares.They flash like firelightand move as swiftly as lightning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The king shouts to his officers;they stumble in their haste,rushing
        to the walls to set up their defenses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The river gates have been torn open!The palace is about to collapse!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Nineveh\u2019s exile has been decreed,and all the servant girls mourn
        its capture.They moan like dovesand beat their breasts in sorrow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Nineveh is like a leaking water reservoir!The people are slipping
        away.\u201CStop, stop!\u201D someone shouts,but no one even looks back.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Loot the silver!Plunder the gold!There\u2019s no end to Nineveh\u2019s
        treasures\u2014its vast, uncounted wealth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon the city is plundered, empty, and ruined.Hearts melt and knees
        shake.The people stand aghast,their faces pale and trembling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where now is that great Nineveh,that den filled with young lions?It
        was a place where people\u2014like lions and their cubs\u2014walked freely
        and without fear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The lion tore up meat for his cubsand strangled prey for his mate.He
        filled his den with prey,his caverns with his plunder.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Judgment against Nineveh"
      content: '  What sorrow awaits Nineveh,the city of murder and lies!She is crammed
        with wealthand is never without victims.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear the crack of whips,the rumble of wheels!Horses\u2019 hooves
        pound,and chariots clatter wildly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See the flashing swords and glittering spearsas the charioteers charge
        past!There are countless casualties,heaps of bodies\u2014so many bodies thatpeople
        stumble over them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All this because Nineveh,the beautiful and faithless city,mistress
        of deadly charms,enticed the nations with her beauty.She taught them all
        her magic,enchanting people everywhere.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am your enemy!\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\u201CAnd now I will lift your skirtsand show all
        the earth your nakedness and shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will cover you with filthand show the world how vile you really
        are.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who see you will shrink back and say,\u2018Nineveh lies in ruins.Where
        are the mourners?\u2019Does anyone regret your destruction?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are you any better than the city of Thebes,[[COMMENT(0)]]situated
        on the Nile River, surrounded by water?She was protected by the river on
        all sides,walled in by water.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>No-amon; </b>also in 3:10.
    - title: 
      content: 'Ethiopia[[COMMENT(0)]] and the land of Egyptgave unlimited assistance.The
        nations of Put and Libyawere among her allies.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cush.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet Thebes fell,and her people were led away as captives.Her babies
        were dashed to deathagainst the stones of the streets.Soldiers threw dice[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to get Egyptian officers as servants.All their leaders were bound in chains.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>They cast lots.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And you, Nineveh, will also stagger like a drunkard.You will hide
        for fear of the attacking enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All your fortresses will fall.They will be devoured like the ripe
        figsthat fall into the mouthsof those who shake the trees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your troops will be as weakand helpless as women.The gates of your
        land will be opened wide to the enemyand set on fire and burned.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Get ready for the siege!Store up water!Strengthen the defenses!Go
        into the pits to trample clay,and pack it into molds,making bricks to repair
        the walls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the fire will devour you;the sword will cut you down.The enemy
        will consume you like locusts,devouring everything they see.There will be
        no escape,even if you multiply like swarming locusts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your merchants have multiplieduntil they outnumber the stars.But
        like a swarm of locusts,they strip the land and fly away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your guards[[COMMENT(0)]] and officials are also like swarming locuststhat
        crowd together in the hedges on a cold day.But like locusts that fly away
        when the sun comes up,all of them will fly away and disappear.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        content: Or <b>princes.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Your shepherds are asleep, O Assyrian king;your princes lie dead
        in the dust.Your people are scattered across the mountainswith no one to
        gather them together.  '
      comments: []
